      "id": "8625348b11718ef3",
      "text": "Karl Weick gives a useful operational definition of commitment. I am probably paraphrasing but my memory of it is:\n \n1) personal, \n2) voluntary, \n3) public, and \n4) irrevocable statement of intentions and agreements.\n\nIn a coalition, don't assume you have commitment without having all parts of this formula for each key stakeholder and leader. Get boards, CEOs, opinion leaders, and frontline staff to tell their stories in a way that fulfill these criteria.\n\nModel it yourself and invite others.\n"
